cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper addresses a societal issue of improving the speed and cost of logistics for online shoppers, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a collaborative approach to package delivery using existing taxis, which involves distributed computing and resource allocation.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper utilizes historical taxi GPS trajectory data to build a package transport network, which involves analyzing and modeling social and information networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an online adaptive taxi scheduling algorithm to find the path with the maximum arriving-on-time probability, which involves machine learning techniques.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper involves developing a probabilistic framework and an online adaptive algorithm for package delivery, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
